{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JPKtB7FpYa1C6upmPbud6U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster now has 9 nodes:\n- es-0 (master*)\n- es-1\n- es-2\n- es-cluster-0 (just joined)\n- es-cluster-1 (just joined)\n- es-cluster-2 (just joined)\n- es-data-0\n- es-data-1\n- es-transform-0\n\nThis is great! All 9 nodes are in the cluster. The `es-http` service (which the oracle uses) routes to `es-data-0` and `es-data-1` (tier=new). But these are showing 0/1 Running in the pod list.\nThe `es-data` pods might be failing their readiness probes. Looking at the StatefulSet config, the `es-data` nodes are configured with roles `[data, ingest]`, so they're not master-eligible nodes.\n\nThe readiness probe is checking TCP connectivity on port 9200, but the pods show as `0/1 Running` even though `_cat/nodes` indicates they're live in the cluster. This suggests the readiness probe might actually be an HTTP check that requires authentication with the elastic password, which could be failing silently. Let me look more closely at the actual readiness probe configuration for the `es-data` StatefulSet.\n\nActually, I'm noticing something important in the earlier output - when everything was working, `es-data-0` and `es-data-1` were both `1/1 Running`. But after the `es-cluster` nodes joined, they dropped to `0/1 Running`, along with the `es-0/1/2` pods. This timing suggests a resource contention issue - the cluster now has 9 nodes consuming significant CPU and memory, and the readiness probes might be timing out or failing under the load.\n\nBut wait, the `_cat/nodes` output shows all 9 nodes are responsive and in the cluster, so the issue might just be temporary readiness probe failures. The key insight is that `es-data-0/1` have HTTP readiness probes while `es-cluster` uses TCP socket probes on port 9200. Since `es-data-0/1` are failing their readiness checks, the `es-http` service won't route traffic to them, which could be blocking queries.\n\nLet me check the readiness probe configuration for the `es-0` and `es-data-0` pods to understand why they're failing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":528,"cache_read_input_tokens":90141,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":528},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b84f9a17-808f-4bbc-883e-f249de9070d1","uuid":"4fbb7557-061a-446e-8bbb-19624648c5aa","request_id":"req_011Cc8zFGMVRVhHqR8YH6DNu"}
